description: Dysphagia, or swallowing disorder, can present as difficulty or pain when swallowing. Dysphagia is most often caused by issues with the muscles used in swallowing or issues with the movement of the bolus through the digestive tract.

description: Common variable immunodeficiency (CVID) is a humoral immunodeficiency disorder characterized by recurrent infections and hypogammaglobulinemia (low level of antibodies). It often has a late onset, which means that it typically first presents with symptoms in adulthood.

description: CGD, or chronic granulomatous disease, refers to a group of inherited disorders that affect the bodys immune system. People with CGD are more likely to get serious infections, often from bacteria and fungi that dont cause problems for healthy people.
description: This common infectious disease, known as mono or the kissing disease, is caused by the Epstein-Barr virus (EBV), and usually affects teenagers and young adults.
description: A group of many different diseases in which part of the bodys immune system is missing or does not work properly.

description: Lymphoma is cancer that begins in lymphocytes, a type of white blood cell. It can begin in the lymphatic tissues, like the spleen, lymph nodes and thymus, or other organs where lymphocytes reside and perform their functions, such as the bone marrow, spleen and blood.

description: Leukemia, is a cancer of blood cells that affects the bodys ability to fight infection. Leukemias are a diverse group, some progress slowly and some are aggressive, and they are most often categorized by the type of white blood cell thats affected and whether it is acute or chronic.
description: Commonly referred to as pompholyx, dyshidrosis, or “bubble eczema,” this type of skin condition is caused by tiny blisters on the palms of the hands or soles of the feet.

description: Irritable bowel syndrome (IBS) is a common disorder that affects the large intestine. Leading to a wide range of gastrointestinal symptoms, IBS is often accompanied by periods of diarrhea, constipation and pain in the abdomen.

description: Graft-versus-host disease (GVHD) is a condition that can occur after a stem cell or bone marrow transplant, when the donors immune cells (graft cells) attack the tissues of your body (host).
